-- Ukraine’s Firtash to Build Titanium Dioxide Plant, Izvestia Says
-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 2012-03-30T06:15:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-30/ukraine-s-firtash-to-build-titanium-dioxide-plant-izvestia-says.html
Ukrainian billionaire Dmitry Firtash’s holding company, Group DF, plans to build a new
titanium dioxide plant in three or four years,  Ekonomicheskie
Izvestia  reported, citing Firtash.  The new plant will have annual titanium dioxide output
capacity of 120,000 tons, according to Kiev-based Izvestia.
Together with ZAT Krymskyi Tytan, titanium dioxide production
will reach 240,000 tons a year by 2016, the newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
